target
artifacts
coverage
# `corpus/` holds committed seed inputs that keep fuzz runs reproducible.
# `cargo fuzz` will write discovered inputs back here too (long opaque
# hex-named files), but we want the curated seeds to ship with the repo.
# Strategy: ignore everything under corpus/<target>/, then re-include any
# file whose name starts with `seed_` regardless of extension (txt, json,
# bin, der, ...).
!corpus/
corpus/*/*
!corpus/*/seed_*
